Package net.ssehub.comani.utility

Class ProcessUtilities.ExecutionResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.ssehub.comani.utility.ProcessUtilities.ExecutionResult
  • Enclosing class:
    ProcessUtilities
    public class ProcessUtilities.ExecutionResult
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides the results of the execution of a command via ProcessUtilities.executeCommand(String[], File). These results subsume the command and the working directory used for the execution of the subprocess, the standard output and error output data provided by this subprocess, the possible exception thrown during the execution of the subprocess, and the exit value of the subprocess.
    Author:
    Christian Kroeher

      • executionSuccessful

        public boolean executionSuccessful()
        Checks whether the execution of the command was successful (true) or not (false). This check will only return true if the processExitValue is 0 and there were no exceptions thrown.
        Returns:
        true if the process executing the command has exit value 0 and no exceptions were thrown; false otherwise
